
import numpy as np
x=np.random.randint(0,10,(3,3))
x

o/p : array([[8, 7, 5],
             [4, 7, 8],
             [9, 4, 3]])

x_sub=x[:2,:2].copy()      # copying the array
x_sub

o/p : array([[8, 7],
             [4, 7]])

  If we now modify this subarray, the original array is not touched:

x_sub[0,1]=3

